    "course_title": "STRESS AND RESILIENCE IN FAMILIES ACROSS THE LIFESPAN",
    "description": "Examines family stress and resilience across the life cycle from psychological,  sociological, and biosocial perspectives. Explores research relating to normative and non-normative family stress and resiliency factors. Topics include parenting, poverty, violence, work-family balance, aging, health and wellness and others.",
